      • retrieveIntValue

        public static int retrieveIntValue(String number,
                                   boolean canBeMissing)
                            throws ParseException
        Retrieves an int value from a Common Log Format field.
        Parameters:
        number - a String int representation
        canBeMissing - indicates if the value can be missing and represented by a hyphen "-".
        Returns:
        0 if no value is provided (represented by a hyphen "-"), the int value otherwise.
        Throws:
        ParseException - if the number is not a valid int representation and is not a hyphen "-".

      • retrieveString

        public static String retrieveString(String value)
        Retrieves a String value from a Common Log Format field and nullify it if not present (represented by a hyphen "-").
        Parameters:
        value - a String representation of the value to retrieve.
        Returns:
        null if the value is a hyphen "-", the String value otherwise.

      • retrieveSection

        public static String retrieveSection(String resource)
                              throws ParseException
        Retrieves the web site section from a resource url. A section is defined as being what's before the second '/' in a URL. i.e. the section for "/pages/create' is "pages")
        Parameters:
        resource - the full resource url value.
        Returns:
        the section name.
        Throws:
        ParseException - if the section is not present or the url has a bad format.
